race.description: Vrc Super Saturday, 7 March F&M Handicap
race.comment: CELERITY (6) couldn't have been much more impressive winning here on New Year's Eve, sitting just off the pace and coming right away to score by nearly four lengths in a clear career peak. Up to 1100m here which she's failed to win at yet, but she only rises 1kg for the slight jump in grade and this looks winnable again. MYSTIC REIGN (3) looks the danger at each way odds. She resumed here over 1000m and found the line well in a dash home. Like her getting to 1100m here and she showed good ability last time in. Expect a much better run. LUNA CAT (1) resumes. She doesn't win out of turn but is very consistent around this level and she does typically go well fresh. OUT OF SQUARE (2) will find this easier than the Black Pearl at Geelong last time. The fresh win in SA was eye catching. EGERTON (4) is consistent and should be thereabouts again.
